The paper deals with pose estimation from volumetric data using deep learning, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of OCT as an imaging modality also suggests a potential fit with medical imaging (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the design of efficient 3D CNN architectures, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
